1
00:00:11,733 --> 00:00:14,567
I'm glad you didn't approach
her yesterday.

2
00:00:14,633 --> 00:00:15,800
My god, I was so worried.

3
00:00:15,867 --> 00:00:17,467
Mookie, I miss you so much.

4
00:00:17,533 --> 00:00:19,667
I miss you so much, too.

5
00:00:19,733 --> 00:00:23,767
I saw it in your mom's office
when Flor and I cleaned it.

6
00:00:23,833 --> 00:00:25,000
You look healthy.

7
00:00:25,067 --> 00:00:26,867
Olive made another order
of Canixidol?

8
00:00:26,933 --> 00:00:29,200
Why are you keeping
this photo in your room?

9
00:00:29,267 --> 00:00:32,300
Why are you angry?
It's just a picture.

10
00:00:32,367 --> 00:00:34,633
I will put her in the darkroom.
Hurry!

11
00:00:34,733 --> 00:00:37,467
Why do you always seem
to want me to be sick?

12
00:00:37,533 --> 00:00:41,567
If you love me,
you won't hurt me!

13
00:00:41,633 --> 00:00:45,800
If you love me,
you want me to get well!

14
00:00:45,867 --> 00:00:48,233
How are you?
Have you found them?

15
00:00:48,300 --> 00:00:50,133
- Do you have any news?
- I don't know yet.

16
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:52,167
The one who told me
doesn't know it, too.

17
00:00:52,233 --> 00:00:56,400
You won't get out of here
until I say so.

18
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:37,567
Emma, here. Have some snacks.

19
00:01:37,633 --> 00:01:39,433
There you go. Go on and eat.
I'll just finish my work inside.

20
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:42,000
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

21
00:02:43,833 --> 00:02:45,600
Flor.

22
00:02:45,667 --> 00:02:48,267
Is Mookie back in her room?

23
00:02:48,367 --> 00:02:50,200
Oh, no, not yet.

24
00:02:50,267 --> 00:02:52,933
She's in the darkroom.

25
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:54,300
Darkroom?

26
00:02:54,367 --> 00:02:58,300
It's just a stockroom
for Ma'am Olive's old stuff.

27
00:02:58,367 --> 00:03:00,200
Why is she there?

28
00:03:00,267 --> 00:03:02,600
That place is okay, it's just...

29
00:03:02,667 --> 00:03:05,033
dark because there's no light.

30
00:03:05,100 --> 00:03:06,033
I don't know why Ma'am Olive

31
00:03:06,100 --> 00:03:08,733
doesn't want
to replace the bulb.

32
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:10,000
Flor.

33
00:03:10,067 --> 00:03:11,533
Can you talk to Ma'am Olive?

34
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:13,367
Mookie is afraid of the dark.

35
00:03:13,433 --> 00:03:14,400
Oh, come on.

36
00:03:14,467 --> 00:03:17,000
What can I do?

37
00:03:17,067 --> 00:03:18,800
She won't listen to me.

38
00:03:18,867 --> 00:03:20,533
Just leave it be.

39
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:22,400
It's just one night.

40
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:24,500
Without food?

41
00:03:24,567 --> 00:03:26,867
Don't worry. She'll let her out
tomorrow morning.

42
00:03:26,933 --> 00:03:28,167
That's how she disciplines
her child.

43
00:03:29,933 --> 00:03:32,033
What kind of discipline is that?

44
00:03:32,100 --> 00:03:34,933
You'll lock your child up
without food?

45
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:35,967
What's wrong with you...

46
00:03:37,667 --> 00:03:43,100
We have our own different ways
of disciplining our children.

47
00:03:43,167 --> 00:03:44,300
What can we do?

48
00:03:44,367 --> 00:03:47,867
She's the mother.
Who are we to oppose?

49
00:03:47,933 --> 00:03:48,900
Just leave it be.

50
00:04:49,833 --> 00:04:50,967
Ma'am Astrid!

51
00:04:51,033 --> 00:04:53,900
Ma'am Astrid!
Wait, can I have a word?

52
00:04:53,967 --> 00:04:56,133
- It's about...
- Let's talk later. Later.

53
00:04:56,200 --> 00:04:57,733
I need to talk to Olive.

54
00:04:57,800 --> 00:04:59,600
But, Ma'am, wait...

55
00:05:03,133 --> 00:05:05,000
Ma'am Astrid, you can't be here.

56
00:05:05,067 --> 00:05:07,767
I'll get scolded
if she catches us here.

57
00:05:07,833 --> 00:05:09,433
I'll talk to her.

58
00:05:09,500 --> 00:05:11,500
Ma'am, please wait outside.

59
00:05:11,567 --> 00:05:13,700
I'll call Ma'am Olive.

60
00:05:13,767 --> 00:05:14,867
Please, Ma'am.
You can't be here.

61
00:05:14,933 --> 00:05:16,867
I'll get scolded.

62
00:05:16,933 --> 00:05:17,900
Ma'am!

63
00:05:17,967 --> 00:05:20,167
I'll be in hot water, Ma'am.

64
00:05:20,233 --> 00:05:22,867
I'll get fired
if she sees us here.

65
00:05:25,733 --> 00:05:28,500
Ma'am, please.
Please wait outside.

66
00:05:32,567 --> 00:05:34,900
What are you doing here, Astrid?

67
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:38,467
Flor, I'll take care of her.

68
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:41,533
Okay. I'm sorry.

69
00:05:43,933 --> 00:05:47,233
You're lucky I let you
return from Cebu.

70
00:05:49,133 --> 00:05:50,700
And here you are...

71
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:55,300
giving me a headache.

72
00:05:56,833 --> 00:05:59,233
I was surprised
by what Grace told me.

73
00:05:59,300 --> 00:06:01,733
Why did you order
a bulk of Canixidol?

74
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:03,900
Is this for Mookie again?

75
00:06:03,967 --> 00:06:05,500
No!

76
00:06:05,567 --> 00:06:08,067
Olive, stop lying.

77
00:06:08,167 --> 00:06:11,933
I know you're using that
for Mookie.

78
00:06:23,867 --> 00:06:27,133
When you feel everything
around you is dark,

79
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:29,567
look up at the sky.

80
00:06:29,633 --> 00:06:31,867
You'll see at least one star.

81
00:06:31,933 --> 00:06:33,600
Shining.

82
00:06:33,667 --> 00:06:35,900
There will be light.

83
00:06:35,967 --> 00:06:37,333
I'm brave.

84
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:38,667
I'm brave.

85
00:06:38,733 --> 00:06:41,700
Mommy Emma said I'm brave.

86
00:06:54,367 --> 00:06:58,667
Don't ever try to mess
with my plans.

87
00:06:58,733 --> 00:07:00,933
Sorry, but we're different.

88
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:03,567
I can no longer tolerate
what you're doing.

89
00:07:03,633 --> 00:07:05,033
So, I'll get this.

90
00:07:05,100 --> 00:07:06,933
Give that to me!
Give that to me!

91
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:10,000
- I said give it to me! Let go!
- No, it's mine.

92
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:13,033
Astrid!

93
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:14,200
Give that to me!

94
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:15,233
Astrid!

95
00:07:58,200 --> 00:07:59,000
Mommy.

96
00:07:59,067 --> 00:08:00,433
Mommy, sorry.

97
00:08:00,500 --> 00:08:03,533
Sorry.

98
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:05,967
Sorry.

99
00:08:06,033 --> 00:08:09,600
Mommy, sorry.

100
00:08:09,667 --> 00:08:10,833
Sorry.

101
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,333
Mommy Emma?

102
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:19,600
Mommy Emma.

103
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:22,133
Mommy Emma!

104
00:08:24,700 --> 00:08:26,867
Mookie.

105
00:08:34,633 --> 00:08:35,700
That's what happened.

106
00:08:35,767 --> 00:08:40,033
Because Wiro refused to pay up
after losing our bet,

107
00:08:40,100 --> 00:08:41,700
do you know what I did?

108
00:08:41,767 --> 00:08:44,633
I snatched the cash
from his hand!

109
00:08:44,700 --> 00:08:46,467
And then what happened?

110
00:08:46,533 --> 00:08:51,000
The money fell
into the pig's poop.

111
00:08:51,067 --> 00:08:53,633
- So disgusting!
- I couldn't get it

112
00:08:53,700 --> 00:08:54,900
because it stinks!

113
00:08:56,567 --> 00:08:57,867
Serves you right.

114
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:05,767
Ligaya, we're running out
of jokes.

115
00:09:05,833 --> 00:09:08,167
And you're still sad?

116
00:09:08,233 --> 00:09:10,667
What exactly are you
talking about

117
00:09:10,733 --> 00:09:12,833
that you can't seem to find?

118
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:18,167
It's because I can't...

119
00:09:24,333 --> 00:09:25,333
What?

120
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:30,433
Emma's not coming home?

121
00:09:30,533 --> 00:09:34,567
This kid. What is it this time?

122
00:09:39,700 --> 00:09:41,500
Are you having a hard
time breathing?

123
00:09:41,567 --> 00:09:43,800
Take a deep breath.
Hold onto your chest.

124
00:09:43,867 --> 00:09:46,133
Hold onto your chest.

125
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:48,467
Hold onto your chest.

126
00:09:48,533 --> 00:09:51,300
There, like this.

127
00:09:51,367 --> 00:09:53,867
Inhale through your nose.

128
00:09:53,933 --> 00:09:56,300
Exhale through your mouth.

129
00:09:56,367 --> 00:09:57,400
Inhale through your nose.

130
00:09:59,167 --> 00:10:00,733
Exhale through your mouth.

131
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:01,700
More.

132
00:10:12,500 --> 00:10:15,733
Think of happy thoughts, go on.
Inhale.

133
00:10:22,967 --> 00:10:23,933
Mookie.

134
00:10:26,933 --> 00:10:28,000
Are you okay?

135
00:10:29,233 --> 00:10:32,400
What happened?
Why is Emma not coming home?

136
00:10:32,467 --> 00:10:34,067
Where is she?

137
00:10:34,133 --> 00:10:36,900
Isn't she at the mansion?
Working at that big house?

138
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:39,533
No. That's why I'm asking
where Emma is.

139
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:40,800
Because she might have left

140
00:10:40,867 --> 00:10:42,367
or something might
have happened.

141
00:10:42,433 --> 00:10:46,367
- We don't know. Right?
- Right.

142
00:10:46,433 --> 00:10:47,933
- Danilo!
- Mother.

143
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:50,067
Did Emma tell you that
she's not coming home?

144
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:52,833
Yes, Mother.

145
00:10:52,900 --> 00:10:54,267
Why?

146
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:01,400
There.

147
00:11:01,467 --> 00:11:04,067
Let's make this our table.

148
00:11:08,667 --> 00:11:10,967
Mommy Emma, I have a question.

149
00:11:11,033 --> 00:11:14,400
Where did you learn what
you did to me earlier?

150
00:11:14,467 --> 00:11:18,933
The one you taught me earlier
to manage my panic attack.

151
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:22,267
I looked up about your
illness on the net.

152
00:11:22,333 --> 00:11:25,633
I've learned something somehow.

153
00:11:25,700 --> 00:11:28,233
You're so impressive,
Mommy Emma.

154
00:11:28,300 --> 00:11:29,700
You know what?

155
00:11:29,767 --> 00:11:32,733
Mommy's giving me
a lot of medicines.

156
00:11:33,967 --> 00:11:39,533
But I just realized
that your love and care

157
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:43,033
is what can calm me down.

158
00:11:43,133 --> 00:11:46,067
At least, I was able to help you
in some way.

159
00:11:47,800 --> 00:11:51,933
Staying here with me is already
a big help, Mommy Emma.

160
00:11:53,233 --> 00:11:56,533
How did you know I'm here?

161
00:11:57,933 --> 00:11:59,533
I heard you
and your mom earlier.

162
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:01,700
That's why I know you're here.

163
00:12:33,533 --> 00:12:34,700
Dan?

164
00:12:34,767 --> 00:12:36,333
Emma?

165
00:12:36,400 --> 00:12:38,533
I have a favor to ask you.

166
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:39,867
I can't come home tonight.

167
00:12:39,933 --> 00:12:41,367
What? Why?

168
00:12:41,433 --> 00:12:43,533
I need to stay with Mookie.

169
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:44,733
What?

170
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:47,000
Why, Emma? What's going on?

171
00:12:47,067 --> 00:12:49,233
I'll explain to you later.

172
00:12:49,333 --> 00:12:50,733
But, Emma...

173
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:54,233
Dan, please don't deny me
the chance to help Mookie.

174
00:12:54,300 --> 00:12:55,467
She needs me now.

175
00:12:59,367 --> 00:13:02,900
He will understand, Mookie.
So you don't have to worry.

176
00:13:02,967 --> 00:13:05,967
Let's focus on your wellness.

177
00:13:06,033 --> 00:13:07,433
So eat.

178
00:13:07,500 --> 00:13:08,567
Don't tire yourself out.

179
00:13:08,633 --> 00:13:11,100
You might have a hard time
breathing again.

180
00:13:11,167 --> 00:13:13,267
You know what, Mommy Emma?

181
00:13:13,333 --> 00:13:18,067
I think the reason
I couldn't breathe earlier

182
00:13:18,133 --> 00:13:20,233
was because
I had a panic attack.

183
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:24,967
Because it's dark here,
and I was scared.

184
00:13:25,067 --> 00:13:26,933
But look at me, Mommy Emma.

185
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:28,167
See?

186
00:13:28,233 --> 00:13:34,167
I still can breathe even
without a cannula and oxygen.

187
00:13:34,233 --> 00:13:38,233
I think you have superpowers.

188
00:13:38,300 --> 00:13:41,900
Because I get better
whenever I'm with you.

189
00:13:43,433 --> 00:13:44,600
Go on and eat.

190
00:13:44,667 --> 00:13:46,367
Here's your water.

191
00:13:46,433 --> 00:13:47,500
There.

192
00:13:56,667 --> 00:13:59,167
Why do you seem sad?

193
00:13:59,233 --> 00:14:00,900
Mommy Emma is here now.

194
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:04,767
It's nothing, Mommy Emma.

195
00:14:05,967 --> 00:14:11,900
You were there
when I had a fever.

196
00:14:11,967 --> 00:14:14,567
And, now...

197
00:14:16,133 --> 00:14:19,267
you're here to be with me.

198
00:14:19,333 --> 00:14:23,067
Mookie, this isn't a big deal.

199
00:14:23,133 --> 00:14:26,900
You're actually
the one doing me a favor.

200
00:14:26,967 --> 00:14:31,100
Because I feel so happy
when I get to help you.

201
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:32,333
You know what, Mommy Emma...

202
00:14:33,367 --> 00:14:35,967
this isn't a small thing.

203
00:14:36,033 --> 00:14:38,433
Because...

204
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:41,967
I remember whenever
I was in this room,

205
00:14:42,033 --> 00:14:43,900
I always felt so scared.

206
00:14:45,167 --> 00:14:47,667
But since you're here now...

207
00:14:49,667 --> 00:14:54,200
I don't feel any fear.

208
00:14:58,600 --> 00:14:59,533
But...

209
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:03,367
I shouldn't get used to it.

210
00:15:04,167 --> 00:15:06,433
Why?

211
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:12,633
Later, when we get
separated again,

212
00:15:12,700 --> 00:15:16,133
I'll miss you so much.

213
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:19,767
Who said we're going
to be apart?

214
00:15:19,833 --> 00:15:23,267
We might get separated
when mommy catches us.

215
00:15:23,333 --> 00:15:26,400
Mommy Emma, I don't want
to be away from you

216
00:15:26,467 --> 00:15:28,200
even if that happens.

217
00:15:29,800 --> 00:15:32,433
We'll never be apart.

218
00:15:32,500 --> 00:15:33,967
That won't happen.

219
00:15:38,867 --> 00:15:41,067
Don't cry, Mommy Emma.

220
00:15:46,533 --> 00:15:47,567
You're unbelievable!

221
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:51,233
You let Emma sleep over
at Madame's place?

222
00:15:51,300 --> 00:15:52,667
Does Ma'am Olive know about it?

223
00:15:54,833 --> 00:15:58,767
I'm not sure, Mother.
Emma's call was interrupted.

224
00:15:58,833 --> 00:16:01,733
Do you know that
I kneeled before Ma'am Olive?

225
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:07,833
I humbled myself just so Emma
could get her job back!

226
00:16:07,900 --> 00:16:09,633
What if Emma
does something again

227
00:16:09,733 --> 00:16:11,100
that Ma'am Olive won't like?

228
00:16:11,167 --> 00:16:12,967
She'll get fired again.

229
00:16:14,767 --> 00:16:16,833
Let's just leave her be, Mother.

230
00:16:16,900 --> 00:16:18,167
Let's leave Emma be.

231
00:16:18,233 --> 00:16:19,767
- What are you talking about?
- That's what makes her happy.

232
00:16:19,833 --> 00:16:21,367
Makes her happy?

233
00:16:22,800 --> 00:16:24,967
Then I have to beg again?

234
00:16:25,033 --> 00:16:26,033
What does she think of me?

235
00:16:26,100 --> 00:16:28,200
A main character
in a drama series?

236
00:16:28,267 --> 00:16:29,433
I won't beg again!

237
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:30,900
You can all deal with it.

238
00:16:36,133 --> 00:16:39,100
I'm not done with you, Astrid.

239
00:16:39,167 --> 00:16:42,100
Prepare yourself
for what I'm going to do.

240
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:07,433
It's mother.

241
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:38,467
Mother.

242
00:17:38,533 --> 00:17:41,567
- Mother!
- Hey! Let go of me.

243
00:17:41,633 --> 00:17:43,833
- Leave Emma be!
- She must come home now!

244
00:17:43,900 --> 00:17:45,933
Mother, leave it be.
Leave Emma be.

245
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:49,500
- Let her spend the night there!
- You're a pain, you animal!

246
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:50,667
If you're just going
to give her a lecture,

247
00:17:50,733 --> 00:17:52,067
do it tomorrow instead. Not now.

248
00:17:52,133 --> 00:17:54,733
Ma'am Olive probably
doesn't know about this.

249
00:17:54,800 --> 00:17:57,633
What if Emma gets caught again?

250
00:17:57,700 --> 00:17:59,433
What will you do?
You're not using your head.

251
00:17:59,500 --> 00:18:03,000
Where's your brain? Did you
deliver it to someone else?

252
00:18:03,067 --> 00:18:04,167
Or maybe, Mother,

253
00:18:04,233 --> 00:18:06,500
I'm just following
what my heart tells me.

254
00:18:06,567 --> 00:18:07,933
Heart, my foot!

255
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:10,000
The heart is only
for playing cards!

256
00:18:11,900 --> 00:18:13,533
I can't stop Emma.

257
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:16,167
No, you're a fool!

258
00:18:16,233 --> 00:18:18,500
Fool!

259
00:18:18,567 --> 00:18:21,733
That's not really
about being foolish.

260
00:18:21,833 --> 00:18:23,933
I've never seen Emma
this happy before,

261
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:26,400
except when she met Mookie.

262
00:18:26,467 --> 00:18:27,733
So I don't care anymore

263
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:32,933
if you think it's foolish for me
to make my wife happy.

264
00:18:35,400 --> 00:18:37,367
I'm doing everything
I can anyway.

265
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:41,700
Here you go, Mother.

266
00:19:06,533 --> 00:19:07,667
It looks like someone's there.

267
00:19:07,733 --> 00:19:08,700
Wait.

268
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:33,800
Mookie?

269
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:40,167
Mookie.

270
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:46,733
Mookie.

271
00:19:50,133 --> 00:19:51,167
Mommy?

272
00:19:53,333 --> 00:19:54,300
Mommy.

273
00:19:55,167 --> 00:19:57,767
Mommy, are you letting me
out now?

274
00:19:57,833 --> 00:19:58,600
No.

275
00:20:01,867 --> 00:20:04,567
I heard a phone ringing.

276
00:20:09,100 --> 00:20:10,867
Are you with someone?

277
00:20:10,933 --> 00:20:13,633
There's no one else here, Mommy.

278
00:20:13,700 --> 00:20:15,400
Maybe you heard this.

279
00:20:16,633 --> 00:20:18,667
I saw it here.

280
00:20:20,667 --> 00:20:22,600
This is my old toy, right?

281
00:20:23,633 --> 00:20:26,200
Are you sure you're alone here?

282
00:20:27,233 --> 00:20:28,300
Yes.

283
00:20:41,933 --> 00:20:43,933
You were so scared back then

284
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:48,900
every time I visited you
here in the darkroom.

285
00:20:48,967 --> 00:20:51,100
You couldn't sleep.

286
00:20:51,167 --> 00:20:53,633
Why is it that now...

287
00:20:53,700 --> 00:20:56,567
you're not affected
that you're in the dark room?

288
00:21:00,900 --> 00:21:03,833
Mommy, that's not true.

289
00:21:03,900 --> 00:21:06,467
Didn't you hear me earlier?

290
00:21:07,833 --> 00:21:09,367
I had a panic attack.

291
00:21:09,467 --> 00:21:11,600
But I overcame it.

292
00:22:09,667 --> 00:22:10,667
What's that?

293
00:22:11,800 --> 00:22:13,500
It's just this, Mommy.

294
00:22:13,567 --> 00:22:15,733
It's just this.

295
00:22:15,833 --> 00:22:17,900
Can you please stop
scaring me like that?

296
00:22:17,967 --> 00:22:19,833
Turn that off!

297
00:22:19,900 --> 00:22:22,233
I was playing with it earlier.

298
00:22:22,300 --> 00:22:25,600
Could it be that this
is what you heard?

299
00:22:27,600 --> 00:22:31,233
It doesn't sound like
what I heard earlier.

300
00:22:53,100 --> 00:22:54,767
Fine.

301
00:22:54,833 --> 00:22:56,333
Whatever.

302
00:22:56,400 --> 00:22:58,033
I'm tired.

303
00:22:58,100 --> 00:22:59,300
I need to go to sleep.

304
00:23:25,667 --> 00:23:28,700
I wish we could get
some medicine.

305
00:23:29,967 --> 00:23:31,067
No need.

306
00:23:31,133 --> 00:23:33,800
Your mom might wake up.

307
00:23:33,867 --> 00:23:36,733
She's taking sleeping pills.

308
00:23:36,800 --> 00:23:39,800
You know, according
to Flor's story,

309
00:23:39,867 --> 00:23:42,667
sometimes she's actually hard
to wake up.

310
00:23:43,700 --> 00:23:45,333
I really hope she's asleep

311
00:23:45,400 --> 00:23:47,367
so she won't come here
to check on us.

312
00:23:53,767 --> 00:23:54,733
Mommy Emma...

313
00:23:56,867 --> 00:23:59,967
don't you want to come home?

314
00:24:00,033 --> 00:24:01,567
You can go home if you like.

315
00:24:01,633 --> 00:24:04,667
So you can treat your wound.

316
00:24:04,733 --> 00:24:07,867
So it won't get infected.

317
00:24:07,933 --> 00:24:10,500
- Dear...
- Only if you like.

318
00:24:10,567 --> 00:24:12,400
This is just a minor wound.

319
00:24:12,467 --> 00:24:15,733
As my mother said,
it's far from the gut.

320
00:24:17,900 --> 00:24:20,967
So I'll just stay here
and keep you company.

321
00:24:24,167 --> 00:24:26,033
Thank you, Mommy Emma.

322
00:24:26,100 --> 00:24:28,933
I won't say no to that.

323
00:24:29,033 --> 00:24:31,367
I want to spend time with you.

324
00:24:33,633 --> 00:24:35,533
You know what, Mommy Emma.

325
00:24:35,600 --> 00:24:38,433
You are so brave.

326
00:24:38,500 --> 00:24:44,067
Even though you're wounded right
now, you're handling the pain,

327
00:24:44,133 --> 00:24:45,800
even if you don't have medicine.

328
00:24:47,333 --> 00:24:48,333
Then...

329
00:24:49,433 --> 00:24:53,800
even though you'll get in
trouble with mommy,

330
00:24:53,867 --> 00:24:56,400
you still visited me here
in the dark room.

331
00:24:58,400 --> 00:24:59,467
Mommy Emma...

332
00:25:01,733 --> 00:25:03,467
What is your secret?

333
00:25:06,633 --> 00:25:09,267
Why are you so brave?

334
00:25:11,900 --> 00:25:14,433
You know what,
when I was a kid...

335
00:25:15,733 --> 00:25:19,667
even though I was scared,
I pretended to be brave.

336
00:25:21,333 --> 00:25:23,500
Why?

337
00:25:23,567 --> 00:25:26,600
Because my mother was not
available to care for me,

338
00:25:26,667 --> 00:25:29,700
that's why I need to be brave.

339
00:25:29,767 --> 00:25:34,233
There's no one to help me,
but myself.

340
00:25:35,933 --> 00:25:38,300
Sorry, Mommy Emma,

341
00:25:38,367 --> 00:25:41,667
I made you sad.

342
00:25:41,733 --> 00:25:43,633
Don't worry, it's nothing.

343
00:25:43,700 --> 00:25:45,100
You know what...

344
00:25:45,167 --> 00:25:47,367
that's something
I want you to learn,

345
00:25:47,433 --> 00:25:50,100
for you to be brave.

346
00:25:50,167 --> 00:25:51,967
Because...

347
00:25:52,033 --> 00:25:54,133
it's not all the time

348
00:25:54,200 --> 00:25:57,200
that I'll be with you
to help you.

349
00:25:57,267 --> 00:26:00,000
I know that, Mommy Emma.

350
00:26:01,867 --> 00:26:05,133
I know it's not that easy,
but...

351
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:08,000
you have to be brave.

352
00:26:16,400 --> 00:26:19,367
How are my children?

353
00:26:19,433 --> 00:26:21,600
I want to see them.

354
00:26:21,667 --> 00:26:26,133
I don't know anything about
your children's whereabouts.

355
00:26:26,200 --> 00:26:30,967
Ma'am, I'm sorry, but your
disciplining methods are wrong.

356
00:26:31,033 --> 00:26:34,933
You shouldn't care how her
mother acts around her child,

357
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:37,833
because you are not the mother,
it's Ma'am Olive.

358
00:26:37,900 --> 00:26:40,067
Whatever your plans are,
no matter what you do,

359
00:26:40,133 --> 00:26:42,067
I won't meddle
in your business anymore.

360
00:26:42,167 --> 00:26:43,167
Just forgive me.

361
00:26:44,100 --> 00:26:47,067
I'm tired of trying
to discipline you.

362
00:26:47,133 --> 00:26:49,667
It's so hard to be your doctor.

363
00:26:49,733 --> 00:26:52,967
Do you have a doctor's license,
Mommy?

364
00:26:54,100 --> 00:26:55,833
Are you really a doctor?
